name: TCB (North East Fork)
description:
Introduction

A great canyon with a relatively short approach and exit. This is not a simply a hike. It is a narrow slot and will requiring squeezing, stemming and some downclimbing. The last section is quite difficult to reverse. A rope can be handy for this.

Approach

Descent

No rappels, but bring 20 feet of webbing for reversing the last downclimb.

This is a great first tight canyon. It's a bit tighter than Middle Leprechaun in places, but always easy to go up and over the constrictions.

Don't miss the dark chamber at the end. Bring a headlight.

Exit

Red tape

properties.description: If you reach this point you've gone too far and need to reverse.

properties.name: Smallcatraz - Approach
properties.description: Note: The route follows a mixture of terrain. A faded, sandy road, single track trail, the wash. There will be lots of intermingled trails for livestock and people. You're aiming for the rancher's watering trough and then you'll veer southeast overland.
